
 * we are able to develop applications everywhere and then
 run it everywhere

 * get all docker images from docker hub,

 * jenkins image contains it's own port: 50000,
 so this might be considered as a server,

 * we are creating instances of images, not images it self

 * container:
 - this is an instance of an image,
 - couple containers might run in the same time,

 * docker file:
 - allows me to create my own docker image

